title: Further Modifying the Reciprocal Tariff Rates

enrichment.summary: This executive order updates and modifies U.S. tariffs on imported goods from certain foreign countries to address trade imbalances and national security concerns. It imposes new and adjusted duties to encourage fair trade, prevent tariff evasion through transshipment, and supports ongoing trade and security negotiations with key partners.
potential_concerns: Increased tariffs may raise costs for American importers and consumers, potentially leading to inflationary pressures.
Retaliatory trade actions by foreign countries could harm U.S. exporters and worsen trade relations.
Enforcement of anti-transshipment measures could lead to disputes and complexities in customs enforcement.
The orderâ€™s broad scope and delegation to multiple agencies may result in inconsistent application or regulatory uncertainty.
Countries on the cusp of agreements might delay negotiations due to ongoing tariffs, slowing resolution of trade disputes.
